This paper deals with the creation of a semantic sketch grammar for specialized information retrieval, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Moreover, the paper mentions the use of knowledge patterns and domain-independent semantic relations, which are common in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Deep Learning (cs.DL) research.
